 source, and reionization model parameters. The 1D\npower spectrum is intrinsically stronger at higher redshifts. A $\\sim 1000$ hr\nobserving campaign targeting $\\sim 100$ narrow sightlines to radio-faint,\nhigh-redshift background objects with modern radio telescopes, especially the\nSquare Kilometre Array, can detect the 1D power spectrum on a range of spatial\nscales and redshifts, and potentially discriminate between models of cosmic\nreionization.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Jun 2020 18:00:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 7 Aug 2020 17:17:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-10"}
