cal universe, we find an\nexcess of BHs with M_BH>10^9 Msun in most of the simulations. The BH mass\nfunction is dominated by efficiently accreting BHs (log10 f_Edd >-2$) at high\nredshifts, and transitions progressively from the high-mass to the low-mass end\nto be governed by inactive BHs. The transition time and the contribution of\nactive BHs are different among the simulations, and can be used to evaluate\nmodels against observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Jun 2020 18:35:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 Nov 2021 18:33:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-03"}
