introduces\nvariations in Ly$\\alpha$ and H$\\alpha$ transits, with H$\\alpha$ variations more\nlikely to be observable. Finally, we show that a strong stellar flare would\nenhance significantly Ly$\\alpha$ and H$\\alpha$ transit depths.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 Jun 2020 15:57:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-01"}
